Note:
==============================================================================
ELEMENT - Generic Markup Element / Attribute / Node Primitive (Tier 1)
==============================================================================

The substrate node types for every markup format Runa replaces - HTML,
XML, SVG, RML, Markdown's embedded HTML blocks, and any tree-shaped
markup document.  The shape mirrors the W3C DOM Level 3 Core
specification (https://www.w3.org/TR/DOM-Level-3-Core/) with explicit
support for XML namespaces (https://www.w3.org/TR/xml-names/) and the
WHATWG DOM Living Standard's flat node model
(https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/).

Representation:
  - Element: a heap record with eight slots (64 bytes).
      slot 0  (off  0):  tag_name pointer        - String, NUL-terminated
      slot 1  (off  8):  namespace pointer       - String or 0
      slot 2  (off 16):  attribute list pointer  - List of Attribute records
      slot 3  (off 24):  child list pointer      - List of MarkupNode records
      slot 4  (off 32):  self_closing flag       - 0 or 1
      slot 5  (off 40):  source_line             - 1-based line number
      slot 6  (off 48):  source_column           - 1-based column number
      slot 7  (off 56):  reserved                - 0

  - Attribute: a heap record with four slots (32 bytes).
      slot 0  (off  0):  name pointer            - String, NUL-terminated
      slot 1  (off  8):  value pointer           - String, NUL-terminated
      slot 2  (off 16):  namespace pointer       - String or 0
      slot 3  (off 24):  reserved                - 0

  - MarkupNode: a heap record with three slots (24 bytes) that tags an
    underlying payload as one of six kinds defined below.
      slot 0  (off  0):  kind                    - NODE_KIND_*
      slot 1  (off  8):  payload pointer         - Element / String / etc.
      slot 2  (off 16):  reserved                - 0

  - DocumentTree: a heap record with four slots (32 bytes).
      slot 0  (off  0):  doctype pointer         - String or 0
      slot 1  (off  8):  root element pointer    - Element
      slot 2  (off 16):  prologue node list      - List of MarkupNode (XML/HTML
                                                   pre-root comments / PIs)
      slot 3  (off 24):  epilogue node list      - List of MarkupNode (post-root
                                                   comments)

Node kinds (DOM Level 3 alignment):
  NODE_KIND_ELEMENT                 1   ELEMENT_NODE
  NODE_KIND_TEXT                    3   TEXT_NODE
  NODE_KIND_COMMENT                 8   COMMENT_NODE
  NODE_KIND_PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION  7   PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE
  NODE_KIND_CDATA_SECTION           4   CDATA_SECTION_NODE
  NODE_KIND_ENTITY_REFERENCE        5   ENTITY_REFERENCE_NODE

Lifetime:
  Every element and node owns its child list and attribute list.
  element_destroy frees the entire subtree.  String slots reference
  caller-owned data when created via the "_with_string" constructors and
  duplicated heap data when created via the duplicating constructors.
  The flag is set on a per-record basis so that element_destroy knows
  whether to free the string payloads.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/char_core.runa" as Char

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant ELEMENT_RECORD_SIZE as Integer is 64
Constant ATTRIBUTE_RECORD_SIZE as Integer is 32
Constant MARKUP_NODE_SIZE as Integer is 24
Constant DOCUMENT_TREE_SIZE as Integer is 32

Constant ELEMENT_OFF_TAG as Integer is 0
Constant ELEMENT_OFF_NAMESPACE as Integer is 8
Constant ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS as Integer is 16
Constant ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN as Integer is 24
Constant ELEMENT_OFF_SELF_CLOSING as Integer is 32
Constant ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_LINE as Integer is 40
Constant ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_COLUMN as Integer is 48
Constant ELEMENT_OFF_RESERVED as Integer is 56

Constant ATTR_OFF_NAME as Integer is 0
Constant ATTR_OFF_VALUE as Integer is 8
Constant ATTR_OFF_NAMESPACE as Integer is 16
Constant ATTR_OFF_RESERVED as Integer is 24

Constant NODE_OFF_KIND as Integer is 0
Constant NODE_OFF_PAYLOAD as Integer is 8
Constant NODE_OFF_RESERVED as Integer is 16

Constant DOCUMENT_OFF_DOCTYPE as Integer is 0
Constant DOCUMENT_OFF_ROOT as Integer is 8
Constant DOCUMENT_OFF_PROLOGUE as Integer is 16
Constant DOCUMENT_OFF_EPILOGUE as Integer is 24

Constant NODE_KIND_ELEMENT as Integer is 1
Constant NODE_KIND_TEXT as Integer is 3
Constant NODE_KIND_COMMENT as Integer is 8
Constant NODE_KIND_PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION as Integer is 7
Constant NODE_KIND_CDATA_SECTION as Integer is 4
Constant NODE_KIND_ENTITY_REFERENCE as Integer is 5

Constant ELEMENT_RESULT_OK as Integer is 0
Constant ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL as Integer is -1
Constant ELEMENT_RESULT_OOM as Integer is -2
Constant ELEMENT_RESULT_NOT_FOUND as Integer is -3

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ATTRIBUTE CONSTRUCTION / ACCESS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct an Attribute record from a name, value, and optional namespace.
W3C DOM Level 3 Core models an attribute as an Attr node; for the markup
substrate the field set collapses to the name-value pair plus the optional
namespace URI per the XML Namespaces 1.1 specification.  All three string
parameters are stored by reference; caller retains ownership and must
keep the storage live for the attribute's lifetime.  A namespace of 0
indicates the no-namespace bucket which is canonical for HTML attributes
without a prefix.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate a 32-byte record.  Write three 64-bit pointer slots and zero the
reserved slot so structural equality on the slot bag works without a
mask.  Return 0 on allocation failure so callers can propagate OOM.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) time, single Layout.allocate.  No string duplication; pure record
assembly.  Heap residency: 32 bytes per attribute.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The constructor accepts arbitrary pointer values without dereferencing
them.  It is the caller's responsibility to ensure the pointers are
either 0 or addresses of valid NUL-terminated UTF-8 strings; misuse
manifests during serialization, not here.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attribute_create" takes name as Integer, value as Integer, namespace as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with ATTRIBUTE_RECORD_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_OFF_NAME, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_OFF_VALUE, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_OFF_NAMESPACE, namespace
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_OFF_RESERVED, 0
    Return record
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the name pointer out of an attribute record.  Provides DOM-style
accessor semantics without exposing the raw memory layout to callers.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct 64-bit load at offset 0.  Returns 0 if the attribute record itself
is 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1), single memory_get_int64 call.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe: 0-valued attribute pointer short-circuits to 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attribute_get_name" takes attribute as Integer returns Integer:
    If attribute is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attribute, ATTR_OFF_NAME
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the attribute's value string pointer.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct 64-bit load at offset 8.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attribute_get_value" takes attribute as Integer returns Integer:
    If attribute is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attribute, ATTR_OFF_VALUE
End Process

@Reasoning
Read the attribute's namespace URI pointer; 0 means the no-namespace
bucket, which is HTML's default for attributes without a colon-prefixed
name.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct 64-bit load at offset 16.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attribute_get_namespace" takes attribute as Integer returns Integer:
    If attribute is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attribute, ATTR_OFF_NAMESPACE
End Process

@Reasoning
Release the attribute record's storage.  Strings are owned by callers,
so this only frees the 32-byte record itself.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.deallocate on the record pointer.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Safe to call with 0 attribute pointer (does nothing).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attribute_destroy" takes attribute as Integer returns Integer:
    If attribute is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with attribute
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MARKUP NODE CONSTRUCTION / ACCESS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a tagged MarkupNode with the given kind and payload pointer.
The node is the union edge over Element / TextNode / Comment / PI /
CDataSection / EntityReference; the payload's interpretation depends on
the kind tag, mirroring DOM Level 3's Node base class.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Allocate 24 bytes.  Write kind and payload pointer; zero reserved slot.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller-supplied kind is not range-checked here; out-of-range tags will
be rejected by every downstream accessor and by the destructor.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_create" takes kind as Integer, payload as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with MARKUP_NODE_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, NODE_OFF_KIND, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, NODE_OFF_PAYLOAD, payload
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, NODE_OFF_RESERVED, 0
    Return record
End Process

@Reasoning
Create an Element-bearing MarkupNode in one step.  Common-case helper.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Calls markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_ELEMENT.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Element pointer is stored verbatim; caller must keep the element alive
until the node is destroyed.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_create_element" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_ELEMENT, element
End Process

@Reasoning
Create a Text MarkupNode whose payload is a borrowed String pointer.
The XML 1.1 specification defines text nodes as the runs of character
data between tags.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Calls markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_TEXT and the supplied string
pointer.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
The string pointer is stored without duplication; caller retains
ownership.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_create_text" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_TEXT, text
End Process

@Reasoning
Create a Comment MarkupNode whose payload is the comment body text
without the surrounding "<!--" / "-->" delimiters.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Calls markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_COMMENT.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Borrowed string pointer.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_create_comment" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_COMMENT, text
End Process

@Reasoning
Create a ProcessingInstruction MarkupNode.  Payload is a List with two
entries: [target_string, data_string], matching XML 1.1 PI structure
(<?target data?>).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Calls markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION; payload
is a borrowed List pointer.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1) for the node creation itself; caller is responsible for the List.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
The List payload must outlive the node, or be transferred by setting the
node's payload to 0 before destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_create_processing_instruction" takes target_and_data_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION, target_and_data_list
End Process

@Reasoning
Create a CDataSection MarkupNode.  CDATA is XML's mechanism for embedding
raw character data without escaping; payload is the raw text body.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Calls markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_CDATA_SECTION.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Borrowed string pointer.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_create_cdata" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_CDATA_SECTION, text
End Process

@Reasoning
Create an EntityReference MarkupNode whose payload is the entity name
without the surrounding "&" and ";".  Used for both predefined XML
entities (&amp;, &lt;, &gt;, &apos;, &quot;) and document-defined entity
references.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Calls markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_ENTITY_REFERENCE.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Borrowed string pointer.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_create_entity_reference" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_ENTITY_REFERENCE, name
End Process

@Reasoning
Retrieve the kind tag from a MarkupNode.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct 64-bit load at offset 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 (an invalid kind) for a 0-valued node, distinguishing it from
any real node kind.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_get_kind" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_KIND
End Process

@Reasoning
Retrieve the payload pointer from a MarkupNode.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct 64-bit load at offset 8.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Interpretation of the returned pointer is the caller's
responsibility per the node's kind tag.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_get_payload" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_PAYLOAD
End Process

@Reasoning
Predicate: is this node an element?  Hot-path discriminator for tree
traversals.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Compare the kind tag against NODE_KIND_ELEMENT.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1), two loads and a compare.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_is_element" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_KIND
    If k is equal to NODE_KIND_ELEMENT:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Predicate: is this node a text node?
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Compare kind tag against NODE_KIND_TEXT.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_is_text" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_KIND
    If k is equal to NODE_KIND_TEXT:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Release a MarkupNode and, for the kinds whose payload it owns
transitively (Element), its payload as well.  Comments, text, CDATA, and
entity reference payloads are caller-owned strings and are NOT freed
here.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
If the node tag is NODE_KIND_ELEMENT, recursively destroy the element
subtree.  Otherwise the payload is left untouched.  Finally Layout.deallocate
the 24-byte record.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(subtree size) when destroying element nodes; O(1) for all other kinds.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller-owned text payloads are preserved.  This avoids double-free when
the same text string is referenced from multiple text nodes (common
during incremental parsing).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_destroy" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_KIND
    Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_PAYLOAD
    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_ELEMENT:
        proc element_destroy with payload
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with node
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ELEMENT CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct an Element record with the supplied tag name and namespace
(both borrowed string pointers).  The attribute list and child list are
freshly allocated empty Lists owned by the element.  This is the primary
constructor for the markup substrate.

self_closing is the boolean that distinguishes "<br/>" from "<div></div>".
HTML void elements are always self-closing; XML elements MAY be when
empty, controlled by the serializer's preference.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate a 64-byte record.  Allocate two backing Lists.  On any
allocation failure undo the partial allocations and return 0.  Source
line and column default to 0 (unknown); callers parsing from text fill
them in via element_set_source_position.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) time, three Layout.allocate calls (record plus two list headers).
Heap residency: 64 bytes for the element record plus the two empty
backing lists from collections/list.runa.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Tag and namespace pointers are borrowed.  Callers that pass dynamically
allocated tag strings must call element_destroy_deep_strings (defined
below) before letting the element drop, or arrange for separate
deallocation of the tag storage.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_create" takes tag_name as Integer, namespace as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with ELEMENT_RECORD_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let attrs be proc list_create from List
    If attrs is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with record
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc list_create from List
    If children is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with attrs
        proc deallocate from Layout with record
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_TAG, tag_name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_NAMESPACE, namespace
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS, attrs
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN, children
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_SELF_CLOSING, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_LINE, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_COLUMN, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ELEMENT_OFF_RESERVED, 0
    Return record
End Process

@Reasoning
Mark the element as self-closing.  HTML void elements (area, base, br,
col, embed, hr, img, input, link, meta, source, track, wbr per WHATWG
HTML 13.1.2) MUST be self-closing.  XML empty elements MAY use the
self-closing shorthand at serialization time.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Write 1 to the self_closing slot.  Idempotent.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_set_self_closing" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SELF_CLOSING, 1
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Record where the element appears in the source text so diagnostics
emitted by downstream tooling (validators, linters) can point at the
correct location.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Write the line and column integers to the corresponding record slots.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Negative inputs are stored verbatim; consumers should treat them as
"unknown".
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_set_source_position" takes element as Integer, line as Integer, column as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_LINE, line
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_COLUMN, column
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ELEMENT ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Return the element's tag name pointer (borrowed).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct load at offset 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_tag_name" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_TAG
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the element's namespace URI pointer; 0 means the no-namespace
bucket.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct load at offset 8.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_namespace" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_NAMESPACE
End Process

@Reasoning
Return a pointer to the element's attribute list.  The list is owned by
the element; callers must not destroy it independently.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct load at offset 16.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_attributes" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
End Process

@Reasoning
Return a pointer to the element's child list.  Same ownership rules as
element_get_attributes.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct load at offset 24.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_children" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the self-closing flag (0 or 1).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct load at offset 32.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_is_self_closing" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SELF_CLOSING
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the 1-based source line number recorded for the element, or 0
when unknown.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct load at offset 40.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_source_line" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_LINE
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the 1-based source column for the element, or 0 when unknown.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Direct load at offset 48.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_source_column" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_COLUMN
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ELEMENT MUTATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Attach a fully-constructed Attribute to an Element.  Insertion order is
preserved per WHATWG DOM Living Standard's NamedNodeMap iteration order
(which the spec defines as insertion order).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Append the attribute pointer to the element's attribute list via
List.list_push.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
Amortized O(1); the underlying List doubles capacity on growth.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe for the element; null attributes are still appended so callers
can model sentinel slots.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_append_attribute" takes element as Integer, attribute as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    Return proc list_push from List with attrs, attribute
End Process

@Reasoning
Look up an attribute by name and return its value pointer, or 0 if no
attribute with that name exists.  This is the DOM Element.getAttribute()
analog.  Comparison is byte-for-byte against the attribute's name slot;
case-insensitivity for HTML must be handled at the caller by lowercasing
the lookup key.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Iterate the attribute list with list_get; for each attribute load the
name slot and compare to the supplied key via StringCore.string_equals.
Return the value slot of the first match.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n) in attribute count.  Typical HTML elements carry fewer than a
handful of attributes, so the linear scan is faster than a hash table
in practice.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Returns 0 (which collides with "attribute present but null
value") only when the attribute is missing; callers needing presence
distinction must call element_has_attribute first.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_attribute" takes element as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    Let count be proc list_length from List with attrs
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let attr be proc list_get from List with attrs, i
        Let attr_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attr, ATTR_OFF_NAME
        Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, name
        If eq is equal to 1:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attr, ATTR_OFF_VALUE
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Test whether an attribute with the given name is present on the element.
Implements DOM Element.hasAttribute().
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Same scan as element_get_attribute but returns 1 on match instead of the
value pointer.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n) in attribute count.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_has_attribute" takes element as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    Let count be proc list_length from List with attrs
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let attr be proc list_get from List with attrs, i
        Let attr_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attr, ATTR_OFF_NAME
        Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, name
        If eq is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a child MarkupNode to the element's children list.  Insertion at
the tail preserves document order, matching the WHATWG DOM appendChild
semantics.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
List.list_push on the children list.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
Amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe for the element; null child is still appended.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_append_child" takes element as Integer, child_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
    Return proc list_push from List with children, child_node
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the number of children attached to the element.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
List.list_length on the children list.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_child_count" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
    Return proc list_length from List with children
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the number of attributes attached to the element.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
List.list_length on the attributes list.
@End Implementation
