@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_attribute_count" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    Return proc list_length from List with attrs
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the child MarkupNode pointer at the given 0-based index, or 0
when the index is out of range.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
List.list_get with bounds checking via list_length.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Out-of-range indices return 0 instead of trapping.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_child" takes element as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
    Let count be proc list_length from List with children
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to count:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_get from List with children, index
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the Attribute pointer at the given 0-based index, or 0 when out
