@End Reasoning
@Implementation
List.list_get with bounds checking via list_length.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Out-of-range indices return 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_get_attribute_at" takes element as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    Let count be proc list_length from List with attrs
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to count:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_get from List with attrs, index
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ELEMENT DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Recursively destroy an element and every node beneath it.  Strings are
caller-owned and untouched; this releases only the records, attribute
records, and node records that the element owns.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
1. Walk the attribute list and free every Attribute record.
2. Walk the child list and call markup_node_destroy on every entry;
   markup_node_destroy itself recurses into Element children.
3. Destroy the backing Lists.
4. Layout.deallocate the 64-byte element record.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(total descendant count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Idempotent against 0 input.  Does not double-free string payloads
because they are borrowed.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_destroy" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    If attrs is not equal to 0:
        Let acount be proc list_length from List with attrs
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than acount:
            Let attr be proc list_get from List with attrs, i
            proc attribute_destroy with attr
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with attrs
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let ccount be proc list_length from List with children
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than ccount:
            Let child be proc list_get from List with children, j
            proc markup_node_destroy with child
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with children
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with element
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DOCUMENT TREE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a DocumentTree with the supplied root element.  Doctype is
optional and may be 0 for XML documents without one or for fragment
trees.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes, write the four slots, allocate the two empty
prologue/epilogue lists.  Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1) plus two list-header allocations.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Doctype and root pointers are borrowed.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_create" takes doctype as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with DOCUMENT_TREE_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prologue be proc list_create from List
    If prologue is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with record
        Return 0
    End If
    Let epilogue be proc list_create from List
    If epilogue is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with prologue
        proc deallocate from Layout with record
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, DOCUMENT_OFF_DOCTYPE, doctype
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, DOCUMENT_OFF_ROOT, root
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, DOCUMENT_OFF_PROLOGUE, prologue
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, DOCUMENT_OFF_EPILOGUE, epilogue
    Return record
End Process

@Reasoning
Doctype accessor (borrowed string pointer or 0).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Load at offset 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_get_doctype" takes doc as Integer returns Integer:
    If doc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_DOCTYPE
End Process

@Reasoning
Root element accessor.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Load at offset 8.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_get_root" takes doc as Integer returns Integer:
    If doc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_ROOT
End Process

@Reasoning
Prologue list accessor - the comments and processing instructions that
appear before the root element in an XML or HTML document.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Load at offset 16.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_get_prologue" takes doc as Integer returns Integer:
    If doc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_PROLOGUE
End Process

@Reasoning
Epilogue list accessor - the comments that appear after the root element.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Load at offset 24.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_get_epilogue" takes doc as Integer returns Integer:
    If doc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_EPILOGUE
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a MarkupNode to the document's prologue.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
List.list_push on the prologue list.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
Amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe for the document.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_append_prologue_node" takes doc as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If doc is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    Let prologue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_PROLOGUE
    Return proc list_push from List with prologue, node
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a MarkupNode to the document's epilogue.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
List.list_push on the epilogue list.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
Amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_append_epilogue_node" takes doc as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If doc is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    Let epilogue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_EPILOGUE
    Return proc list_push from List with epilogue, node
End Process

@Reasoning
Recursively destroy an entire document tree: root element subtree,
prologue and epilogue node lists, and the document record itself.
Doctype string is caller-owned.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Walk prologue and epilogue lists destroying each node, destroy the
backing lists, destroy the root element, free the document record.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(total node count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Doctype string is preserved.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "document_destroy" takes doc as Integer returns Integer:
    If doc is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    Let prologue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_PROLOGUE
    If prologue is not equal to 0:
        Let pcount be proc list_length from List with prologue
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than pcount:
            Let pnode be proc list_get from List with prologue, i
            proc markup_node_destroy with pnode
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with prologue
    End If
    Let epilogue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_EPILOGUE
    If epilogue is not equal to 0:
        Let ecount be proc list_length from List with epilogue
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than ecount:
            Let enode be proc list_get from List with epilogue, j
            proc markup_node_destroy with enode
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with epilogue
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with doc, DOCUMENT_OFF_ROOT
    proc element_destroy with root
    proc deallocate from Layout with doc
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TRAVERSAL - DEPTH-FIRST WALK
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Append every descendant Element of `root` (and `root` itself) to the
caller-supplied output list in depth-first pre-order.  Text, comment, and
other non-element nodes are not appended; only elements participate in
the walk because element traversal is the common case for query engines
(selector matching) and validators.  Pre-order matches the document-order
traversal defined by WHATWG DOM section 4.2.2 and is what CSS selector
matching (Selectors Level 4 section 4) requires.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Iterative two-stack DFS to avoid Runa-stack pressure on deep documents:
push the root, then pop-and-emit while pushing children in reverse so
that the leftmost child is popped first.  A scratch List provides the
work-stack.  Bails out cleanly with ELEMENT_RESULT_OOM if the work-stack
allocation fails.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n) in total element count.  One List allocation for the work stack,
freed before return.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Visits only nodes whose kind is NODE_KIND_ELEMENT, so a
malformed payload pointer attached to a non-element node will never be
dereferenced.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_walk" takes root as Integer, out_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    If out_list is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    Let stack be proc list_create from List
    If stack is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OOM
    End If
    proc list_push from List with stack, root
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let stack_len be proc list_length from List with stack
        If stack_len is equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with stack
            Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
        End If
        Let top_index be stack_len minus 1
        Let elem be proc list_get from List with stack, top_index
        proc list_remove from List with stack, top_index
        If elem is not equal to 0:
            proc list_push from List with out_list, elem
            Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with elem, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
            If children is not equal to 0:
                Let ccount be proc list_length from List with children
                Let idx be ccount minus 1
                While idx is greater than or equal to 0:
                    Let child_node be proc list_get from List with children, idx
                    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with child_node, NODE_OFF_KIND
                    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_ELEMENT:
                        Let child_elem be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with child_node, NODE_OFF_PAYLOAD
                        proc list_push from List with stack, child_elem
                    End If
                    Set idx to idx minus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with stack
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Find every element under `root` whose tag name equals the supplied
NUL-terminated key, returning a freshly allocated List of element
pointers in document order.  Mirrors the DOM Element.getElementsByTagName
collection but materialized as a List instead of as a live HTMLCollection.
Comparison is byte-for-byte using StringCore.string_equals; HTML's
ASCII-case-insensitive matching is the caller's responsibility (pass a
lowercased key against a tree whose tag names have been lowercased on
parse).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Walk the tree with element_walk to gather all elements, then filter by
tag-name equality into a result List.  The scratch list is freed before
return; the result list is owned by the caller and must be destroyed
with list_destroy.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n) traversal + O(n) filter.  Two list allocations.  Element tag names
are short, so the equality check is fast.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Returns 0 on allocation failure so callers can distinguish
OOM from "no matches" (an empty non-zero list).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_find_by_tag" takes root as Integer, tag_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If tag_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let all_elems be proc list_create from List
    If all_elems is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc element_walk with root, all_elems
    Let result be proc list_create from List
    If result is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with all_elems
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with all_elems
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let elem be proc list_get from List with all_elems, i
        Let elem_tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with elem, ELEMENT_OFF_TAG
        Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with elem_tag, tag_name
        If eq is equal to 1:
            proc list_push from List with result, elem
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with all_elems
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Locate the first element whose `id` attribute equals the supplied key, or
0 if no element carries that id.  Mirrors DOM Document.getElementById.
The id attribute is identified by its canonical name "id" per the HTML
Living Standard section 3.2.6; XML id attributes following the
xml:id Recommendation (https://www.w3.org/TR/xml-id/) are not picked up
by this primitive — callers needing XML id semantics must compose their
own query using element_walk and element_get_attribute.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Walk all elements into a scratch list, scan in document order, return
the first element whose "id" attribute value equals the key.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n).  Could be accelerated with an id index, but production HTML
documents rarely have enough ids to justify the table overhead.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Returns 0 for both "not found" and "OOM during walk", which
is acceptable because the result is either a valid pointer or sentinel
zero.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_find_by_id" takes root as Integer, id_value as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If id_value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let all_elems be proc list_create from List
    If all_elems is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc element_walk with root, all_elems
    Let id_key be "id"
    Let count be proc list_length from List with all_elems
    Let i be 0
    Let found be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let elem be proc list_get from List with all_elems, i
        Let val be proc element_get_attribute with elem, id_key
        If val is not equal to 0:
            Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with val, id_value
            If eq is equal to 1:
                Set found to elem
                Set i to count
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with all_elems
    Return found
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SERIALIZATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Append `count` space characters to the StringBuilder used for pretty-
printing element trees.  Two spaces per indent level is the convention
used by the JSON specification (RFC 8259) when authors want indentation
and by the prevailing HTML formatter community.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
While loop appending the space character (32) `count` times.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(count); typical indent depths are < 10.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe builder.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_append_indent" takes sb as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Append an attribute's value enclosed in double quotes, escaping the
characters defined by HTML5 section 8.1.2.3 attribute serialization:
ampersand and quote.  Newlines are escaped using &#10; to keep the
serialized form on a single line.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Iterate the value string by character, write the escape sequence for
each special character, write the raw byte otherwise.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).  No allocations beyond the StringBuilder's growth.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_append_attr_value" takes sb as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
    If value is equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i
        If ch is equal to 38:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&amp;"
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 34:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&quot;"
            Otherwise:
                If ch is equal to 60:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&lt;"
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 62:
                        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&gt;"
                    Otherwise:
                        If ch is equal to 10:
                            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&#10;"
                        Otherwise:
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Recursive pretty-printer.  Emits a self-closing tag for void elements,
a `<tag attrs/>` opening followed by indented children and a closing
tag for normal elements.  Text, comment, CDATA, processing-instruction,
and entity-reference children are emitted in HTML5 serialization form.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
1. Indent + `<tag` + attributes inline.
2. If self_closing or zero children: `/>` then newline.
3. Otherwise: `>` then newline; walk children with indent+1; indent + `</tag>` + newline.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(total subtree size).  StringBuilder amortizes allocations.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Text payloads are escaped via element_append_text.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_append_text_escaped" takes sb as Integer, text as Integer returns Integer:
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If ch is equal to 38:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&amp;"
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 60:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&lt;"
            Otherwise:
                If ch is equal to 62:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "&gt;"
                Otherwise:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

Process called "element_serialize_node" takes sb as Integer, node as Integer, indent as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_KIND
    Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_PAYLOAD
    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_TEXT:
        proc element_append_indent with sb, indent
        proc element_append_text_escaped with sb, payload
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_COMMENT:
        proc element_append_indent with sb, indent
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "<!--"
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, payload
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "-->"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_CDATA_SECTION:
        proc element_append_indent with sb, indent
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "<![CDATA["
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, payload
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "]]>"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_ENTITY_REFERENCE:
        proc element_append_indent with sb, indent
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 38
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, payload
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 59
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_ELEMENT:
        proc element_serialize_element with sb, payload, indent
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

Process called "element_serialize_element" takes sb as Integer, element as Integer, indent as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_NULL
    End If
    proc element_append_indent with sb, indent
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 60
    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_TAG
    If tag is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, tag
    End If
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    If attrs is not equal to 0:
        Let acount be proc list_length from List with attrs
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than acount:
            Let attr be proc list_get from List with attrs, i
            Let aname be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attr, ATTR_OFF_NAME
            Let avalue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with attr, ATTR_OFF_VALUE
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
            If aname is not equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, aname
            End If
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 61
            proc element_append_attr_value with sb, avalue
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Let self_close be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SELF_CLOSING
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
    Let child_count be 0
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Set child_count to proc list_length from List with children
    End If
    If self_close is equal to 1:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "/>"
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    If child_count is equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 62
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "</"
        If tag is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, tag
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 62
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
        Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 62
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than child_count:
        Let child_node be proc list_get from List with children, j
        proc element_serialize_node with sb, child_node, indent plus 2
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    proc element_append_indent with sb, indent
    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "</"
    If tag is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, tag
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 62
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
    Return ELEMENT_RESULT_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Public entry point: serialize an element subtree to a newly-allocated
NUL-terminated String.  The caller owns the returned string and must
release it via the memory layer used by stringbuilder_to_string.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Create a StringBuilder, recurse via element_serialize_element starting
at the supplied indent, materialize the buffer with stringbuilder_to_string,
release the builder.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(total subtree size + total text length).  One StringBuilder + one
output string allocation.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Returns 0 on OOM or null root.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "element_to_string" takes root as Integer, indent_level as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc element_serialize_element with sb, root, indent_level
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DEEP CLONE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Recursively duplicate an element subtree.  String slots are shared with
the original because the substrate treats strings as caller-owned; the
clone references the same byte storage.  Callers needing fully
independent strings must compose their own duplication using the
StringCore primitives.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Allocate a fresh element record with the same tag + namespace.  Copy
the self-closing flag, source line, and source column.  Walk the
original's attribute list and append clones of each attribute.  Walk
the original's child list and clone each node, recursing into elements.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(total descendant count).  No string copies — pointers shared with
source.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Returns 0 on OOM; partial allocations are torn down via
element_destroy so the heap stays consistent.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "markup_node_clone" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_KIND
    Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, NODE_OFF_PAYLOAD
    If kind is equal to NODE_KIND_ELEMENT:
        Let cloned_elem be proc element_clone with payload
        If cloned_elem is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc markup_node_create with NODE_KIND_ELEMENT, cloned_elem
    End If
    Return proc markup_node_create with kind, payload
End Process

Process called "element_clone" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_TAG
    Let ns be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_NAMESPACE
    Let clone be proc element_create with tag, ns
    If clone is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let self_close be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SELF_CLOSING
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with clone, ELEMENT_OFF_SELF_CLOSING, self_close
    Let src_line be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_LINE
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with clone, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_LINE, src_line
    Let src_col be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_COLUMN
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with clone, ELEMENT_OFF_SOURCE_COLUMN, src_col
    Let attrs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_ATTRS
    If attrs is not equal to 0:
        Let acount be proc list_length from List with attrs
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than acount:
            Let src_attr be proc list_get from List with attrs, i
            Let aname be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src_attr, ATTR_OFF_NAME
            Let avalue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src_attr, ATTR_OFF_VALUE
            Let ans be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src_attr, ATTR_OFF_NAMESPACE
            Let cloned_attr be proc attribute_create with aname, avalue, ans
            If cloned_attr is equal to 0:
                proc element_destroy with clone
                Return 0
            End If
            proc element_append_attribute with clone, cloned_attr
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with element, ELEMENT_OFF_CHILDREN
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let ccount be proc list_length from List with children
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than ccount:
            Let src_node be proc list_get from List with children, j
            Let cloned_node be proc markup_node_clone with src_node
            If cloned_node is equal to 0:
                proc element_destroy with clone
                Return 0
            End If
            proc element_append_child with clone, cloned_node
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return clone
End Process
